sources.title: Jacktown (1962) PATTY McCOMACK
sources.description:
Movie Class by PizzaFLIX: Patty McCormack began her career as a child actress and is best known for her performance psychological drama THE BAD SEED (1956).

Stars: Patty McCormack, Richard Meade, Douglas Rutherford 
Writer/Director: William Martin

A juvenile delinquent is sent to prison after he's caught with an underage girl who lied about her age. Co-stars Patty "The Bad Seed" McCormack, the youngest actress to be nominated for an Academy Award.

metadata.Plot: A young delinquent is sent to prison for a statutory rape.
